            "authors": ["Conner"],
            "description": "Metroid FreezeFlame 2: Twisted Dimensions is the sequel to the 2020 released hack Metroid FreezeFlame. In comparison to the first entry in the FreezeFlame series, this hack is not entirely a heat run. Only a short portion in the beginning requires forced damage through heat! The hack was created for the Metroid Construction One Week Contest, which gave contestants one week to create a ROM-Hack or Fangame from scratch. FreezeFlame 2 is a unique hack since it uses the portal elements from FreezeFLame 1 to put the players in worlds formerly only known from other ROM-Hacks. It is reccommended that the player is at least a bit familiar with other Metroid: Zero Mission ROM-Hacks to have a truly good time with this hack.",
        
